HEADWORD: Pricket
<hw>Prick"et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Perhaps so called
from the state of his horns. See <er>Prick</er>, and cf.
<er>Brocket</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A buck in his second
year. See <er>Note</er> under 3d <er>Buck</er>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

